OL,4,Cbreasts removed as cancer diagnosis
OL,5,Cmissed
OL,7,FA mother has told how she went through
OL,8,Fthe trauma of having both breasts
OL,9,Fremoved after doctors failed to spot
OL,10,Fcancer.
OL,12,FSerena Russo, 54, from Sussex has a
OL,13,Ffamily history of cancer so when she
OL,14,Ffound a lump, her GP referred her
OL,15,Fstraight away for a medical
OL,16,Fexamination.
OL,18,FShe attended Worthing Hospital for a
OL,19,Fmammogram during a Covid lockdown,
OL,20,Fwhen she was told her results had come
OL,21,Fback as normal.
